data.description: Step into history with this charming stone farmhouse, a captivating 1768-built home nestled on 1.37 acres of private bliss. This historic gem boasts a rich tapestry of stories, having witnessed the echoes of a distillery, Graham’s Mill, and an inn in its storied past. With exposed beams, a rustic stone fireplace, and stone exterior, each corner exudes character.  Nature enthusiasts will be enchanted by the property's natural wonders—bordered by the meandering Gooseneck Creek, decorated with mature black walnut trees, a graceful mimosa tree, and a symphony of honeysuckle. Wildlife flourishes in this tranquil haven.  The residence itself offers a cozy haven with 3 bedrooms and 2.5 bathrooms. Additionally, three outbuildings on the property provide versatile spaces for your imagination to roam. This property is also zoned C1 mixed use commercial. Could be lodge, boarding, place of worship, retail business, etc. Check with the twp for requirements .
